President Obama placed calls to Senators Graham, McCain, and Rubio to discuss their commitment to bipartisan immigration reform. He commended the Senators for the progress being made by the Gang of 8 and reiterated his support for their efforts. The President emphasized the need for strengthening border security, creating a path to citizenship, holding employers accountable, and streamlining legal immigration. He also mentioned his willingness to submit his own legislation if Congress fails to act. The President thanked the Senators for their leadership and expressed his desire to continue working together to achieve reform. He did not speak with Senator Flake but looks forward to discussing the issue with him soon.